{title: Carolina Star}
{artist: Tony Rice}
{composer: Written by Hugh Moffatt}

[C]Back in the hills those [F]slow rollin’ hills
Where [C]North Carolina comes [G7]close to the stars
There’s [C]livin’ a lady who’s [F]shinin’ so high
They [G7]call her the Carolina [C]Star
She works at the factory from [F]Monday through Friday
She’s [C]raisin’ three daughters [G7]alone
Their [C]daddy’s away he’s [F]chasing a dream
They’re [G7]waitin’ for the day that he comes [C]home
[G7]Oh Caro[F]lin[C]a
Even [F]stars get [G7]lonesome now and [C]then
[G7]Oh Caro[F]lin[C]a
Don’t you [F]worry he’ll be [G7]comin’ home [C]again
He’s playin’ his songs in [F]Nashville
He’s [C]pickin’ for tips in a [G7]bar
He’s [C]broke and all alone but he ain’t [F]ready to come home
He’s [G7]gonna be a bluegrass pickin’ [C]star
Repeat #3
Sometimes she wakes up just [F]thinking of him
She [C]remembers him beside her in the [G7]night
While [C]out across those hills that old [F]moon is settled in
